        "sub_title": "",
        "composer": "Johan de Meij",
        "instrumentation": "Brass Band",
        "synopsis": "<p>\\r\\n\tAfter <strong>Extreme Makeover, Sinfonietta No. 1</strong> is<em> </em>my second original composition for brass band. Both works were commissioned for major competitions. <strong>Extreme Makeover </strong>was written for the top division of the European Brass Band Championships 2005 in Groningen - The Netherlands. <strong>Sinfonietta </strong>was composed for the 3<sup>rd</sup> division of the Dutch National Championships 2011, also held in Groningen. It also served as the test piece for the 3<sup>rd</sup> division of the Swiss National Championships 2011 in Montreux, Switzerland.<br />\\r\\n\tUnlike most of my compositions, <strong>Sinfonietta No. 1</strong> is an abstract, non-programmatic work. It consists of three movements, in which the thematic material of the opening measures &ndash; an upward fifth jump &ndash; returns in various shapes and forms throughout the piece. The slow middle section features solo passages by E-flat tuba, flugelhorn and euphonium, all starting with the same fifth jump. The final movement presents an Elgar-like march theme, interspersed with quotes from the second movement, and ending with the opening theme of movement I.</p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\tJohan de Meij</p>\\r\\n",
