        "synopsis": "<p>\\r\\n\tSince many centuries Poland boasts a very rich tradition as to Christmas Carols. Some hymns belong to the church music, while others definitely do have a folk music character. I have used both these elements in my suite. You can hear successively the songs: Poklon Jezusowi; Mizerna, cicha; Aniol pasterzom m&oacute;wil; Gdy sliczna Panna and Jam jest dudka.</p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\t<em>Commissioned by The American School of the Hague, Arts Director James Yarnell, for the 20th Annual International Honor Band and Choir Festival 1995. World Premiere performance conducted by Dennis Johnson - Choir Director: Doug Nichol.</em></p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\t<strong>Instrumentation</strong><br />\\r\\n\t[Symphonic Band]<br />\\r\\n\t1. Full Score + Condensed Score (C)<br />\\r\\n\t1. Piccolo (C)<br />\\r\\n\t5. Flutes I/II (C)<br />\\r\\n\t2. Oboes I/II (C)<br />\\r\\n\t1. English Horn (F)<br />\\r\\n\t2. Bassoons I/II (C)<br />\\r\\n\t<br />\\r\\n\t1. Eb Clarinet<br />\\r\\n\t6. Clarinet I (Bb)<br />\\r\\n\t6. Clarinet II (Bb)<br />\\r\\n\t6. Clarinet III (Bb)<br />\\r\\n\t1. Eb Alto Clarinet<br />\\r\\n\t1. Bb Bass Clarinet<br />\\r\\n\t<br />\\r\\n\t2. Alto Sax I (Eb)<br />\\r\\n\t2. Alto Sax II (Eb)<br />\\r\\n\t2. Tenor Sax (Bb)<br />\\r\\n\t1. Baritone Sax (Eb)<br />\\r\\n\t<br />\\r\\n\t3. Horn I/III (F)<br />\\r\\n\t3. Horn II/IV (F)<br />\\r\\n\t3. Trumpet I (Bb)<br />\\r\\n\t3. Trumpet II (Bb)<br />\\r\\n\t3. Trumpet III (Bb)<br />\\r\\n\t<br />\\r\\n\t2. Trombone I (C)<br />\\r\\n\t2. Trombone II (C)<br />\\r\\n\t2. Trombone III (C)<br />\\r\\n\t2. Baritone/Euphonium (C)<br />\\r\\n\t2. Bass Tuba (C)<br />\\r\\n\t1. String Bass<br />\\r\\n\t<br />\\r\\n\t1. Timpani<br />\\r\\n\t4. Percussion I &amp; II<br />\\r\\n\t2. Percussion III [Bells, Tubular Bells]<br />\\r\\n\t2. Harp &amp; Church Organ (ad lib.)<br />\\r\\n\t&nbsp;<br />\\r\\n\t<strong>Additional Parts:</strong><br />\\r\\n\t2. Horn I/III in Eb<br />\\r\\n\t2. Horn II/IV in Eb<br />\\r\\n\tin treble- and bass clef:<br />\\r\\n\t2. Trombone I in Bb<br />\\r\\n\t2. Trombone II in Bb<br />\\r\\n\t2. Trombone III in Bb<br />\\r\\n\t2. Baritone/Euph. in Bb<br />\\r\\n\t2. Bass Tuba in Eb<br />\\r\\n\t3. Bass Tuba in Bb</p>\\r\\n",
