        "cd_name": "Ceremonial Fanfare (for brass band)",
        "sub_title": "",
        "composer": "Johan de Meij",
        "instrumentation": "Brass Band",
        "synopsis": "<p>\\r\\n\tThe Ceremonial Fanfare was originally written for orchestral brass and percussion, commissioned by The Orchestra Osaka Symphoniker from Osaka, Japan. The world premi&egrave;re performance took place on April 12, 2005 at The Symphony Hall in Osaka, conducted by maestro Heiichiro Ohyama.</p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\tIn April 2009, the combined brass sections of the New York Philharmonic and the Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra gave an impressive performance in New York City. The concert commemorated the Henry Hudson Quadricentennial and 400 years of friendship between The United States and The Netherlands.</p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\tThis version for brass band was written at the request of EBBC, the European Brass Band Contest 2012 in Rotterdam, to serve as the opening fanfare of the festival.</p>\\r\\n<p style=\"margin-left: 8pt;\">\\r\\n\tInstrumentation:<br />\\r\\n\t1. Eb Soprano Cornet<br />\\r\\n\t4. Solo Bb Cornets<br />\\r\\n\t1. Repiano Bb Cornet<br />\\r\\n\t2. 2<sup>nd</sup> Bb Cornets<br />\\r\\n\t2. 3<sup>rd</sup> Bb Cornets<br />\\r\\n\t1. Bb Flugelhorn<br />\\r\\n\t1. Solo Eb Horn<br />\\r\\n\t1. 1<sup>st</sup> Eb Horn<br />\\r\\n\t1. 2<sup>nd</sup> Eb Horn<br />\\r\\n\t1. 1<sup>st</sup> Bb Baritone<br />\\r\\n\t1. 2<sup>nd</sup> Bb Baritone<br />\\r\\n\t1. 1<sup>st</sup> Bb Trombone<br />\\r\\n\t1. 2<sup>nd</sup> Bb Trombone<br />\\r\\n\t1. Bass Trombone (C)<br />\\r\\n\t1. 1<sup>st </sup>Bb Euphonium<br />\\r\\n\t1. 2<sup>nd</sup> Bb Euphonium<br />\\r\\n\t2. Eb Bass Tubas&nbsp;<br />\\r\\n\t2. Bb Bass Tubas&nbsp;<br />\\r\\n\t2. Tubular Bells, &amp; Suspended Cymbal<br />\\r\\n\t1. Timpani<br />\\r\\n\t2. Large Tam-tam &amp; Cymbals a2</p>\\r\\n",
