        "cd_name": "American Suite - AntonÃ­n DvoÅ™Ã¡k",
        "sub_title": "(Opus 98b)",
        "composer": "AntonÃ­n DvoÅ™Ã¡k - arranged by Johan de Meij",
        "instrumentation": "wind orchestra",
        "synopsis": "<p>\\r\\n\tClick <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8RRwemHpsFk\">HERE</a> to listen &amp; watch the score with SCOREPLAY.</p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\tAnton&iacute;n DvoÅ™&aacute;k&#39;s stay in the United States is invariably associated with his 9th Symphony &quot;From the New World&#39;, but his famous Cello Concerto, his &#39;American&#39; String Quartet and the Piano Suite (opus 98) were also composed in the period from 1892 to 1895, when DvoÅ™&aacute;k was artistic director of the Conservatory in New York. DvoÅ™&aacute;k himself orchestrated the suite one year after the completion of the original version, and gave it the title &quot;American Suite&quot; (Op 98b). His famous Slavonic Dances and Legends were also originally piano works that he orchestrated later. Unfortunately, DvoÅ™&aacute;k never heard the orchestral version. The premiere took place six years after his death on March 1, 1910 in Prague, DvoÅ™&aacute;k&#39;s final resting place.<br />\\r\\n\t<br />\\r\\n\tDvoÅ™&aacute;k&#39;s main goal in America was his quest for authentic &quot;American music&quot; - as he used the Czech folk music earlier in his own compositions. Thanks to his student Harry Burleigh, one of the first African-American composers, DvoÅ™&aacute;k became acquainted with the traditional American spirituals. DvoÅ™&aacute;k was convinced that the Americans would find their own national style through the music of African-Americans and Native Americans. There are clear influences of this American folk music to be found in the American Suite. As in the &quot;New World&quot; symphony and string quartet, DvoÅ™&aacute;k makes extensive use of the pentatonic scale and syncopated rhythms.</p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\tThis arrangement for wind orchestra of the American Suite consists of the following five movements:<br />\\r\\n\t<br />\\r\\n\t<em>1.</em><em>Andante con moto<br />\\r\\n\t2. Allegro<br />\\r\\n\t3. Moderato (alla Pollacca)<br />\\r\\n\t4. Andante<br />\\r\\n\t5. Finale - Allegro</em></p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\t&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n",
